<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-14216] node map does not handle InetAddressAndPort correctly.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14216</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Collection of node information in nodeMap does not use the correct types for accessing data. Since these maps are keyed by Strings, they are not metatype-safe, and so i can&apos;t be certain what data was meant to be in them. I&apos;m assuming it was meant that host and port information should be used, but perhaps it&apos;s just host.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have created a patch&#160;assuming it&apos;s host and port info.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
